{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"padding"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"edges"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge","text":"Edge","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","text":"Set","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO3SetV"},{"kind":"text","text":" = .all, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"length"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The set of edges to pad for this view. The default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set\/all"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"edges"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An amount, given in points, to pad this view on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified edges. If you set the value to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", OpenSwiftUI uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a platform-specific default amount. The default value of this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"name":"length"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that’s padded by the specified amount on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified edges.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier to add a specified amount of padding to one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"edges of the view. Indicate the edges to pad by naming either a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value from ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or by specifying an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/Swift\/OptionSet","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contains edge values:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text padded by 20 points on the bottom and trailing edges.\")","        .padding([.bottom, .trailing], 20)","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The order in which you apply modifiers matters. The example above"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applies the padding before applying the border to ensure that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"border encompasses the padded region:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can omit either or both of the parameters. If you omit the ","type":"text"},{"code":"length","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"OpenSwiftUI uses a default amount of padding. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"omit the ","type":"text"},{"code":"edges","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", OpenSwiftUI applies the padding to all edges. Omit both","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to add a default padding all the way around a view. OpenSwiftUI chooses a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default amount of padding that’s appropriate for the platform and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the presentation context.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text with default padding.\")","        .padding()","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above looks like this in iOS under typical conditions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To control the amount of padding independently for each edge, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/padding(_:)-6pgqq"},{"text":". To pad all outside edges of a view by a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified amount, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/padding(_:)-68shk"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds an equal padding amount to specific edges of this view."}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"padding(_:_:)","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE7paddingyQrAA4EdgeO3SetV_14CoreFoundation7CGFloatVSgtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:11OpenSwiftUI6Slider